## Requirement 1.

### How does the current sales projection differs from the projection.

To analyze the difference in the current sales, we will compute the percentage increase in the sales.

The formula is presented as follows.


$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of increase} &= \dfrac{\text{Est rev for next year - Current rev for the year}}{\text{Current revenue for the year}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Now, let us compute the difference in the sales growth of the company:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Sales Growth}&=\text{Next Year Projections}-\text{Current Year}\\[12pt]
&={3.30\%}-{1.10\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{2.20\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The difference in the sales growth of the company is 2.20\%.**
